Paper: hep-th/9405032

Date: 1994-05-02

Title: Fermion Scattering off Dilatonic Black Holes

Authors: A. GHOSH and P. MITRA (Saha Institute of Nuclear Physics, Calcutta)

Comments: SINP/TNP/94-05

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D50 (1994) 7389-7393

The scattering of massless fermions off magnetically charged dilatonic blackholes is reconsidered and a violation of unitarity is found. Even for a singlespecies of fermion it is possible for a particle to disappear into the blackhole with its information content.